[{"location":"#Synchrotron_General.jl-Documentation","page":"Home","title":"Synchrotron_General.jl Documentation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"j_nu(mps, ν)","category":"page"},{"location":"#SyncSSCModel.j_nu-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"Home","title":"SyncSSCModel.j_nu","text":"j_nu(mps, ν)\n\nGeneral equation of the volume emissivity of synchrotron radiation at frequency ν for parameters mps.\n\nEquation from the book of Longair (1994)\n\nj_nu dnu = -left( fracdEdt right) N(E) dE propto kappa B^alpha+1 nu^-alpha dnu\n\nwhere, the average energy loss rate for ultra-relativistic electron is equal to\n\n-left( fracdEdt right) = frac43 sigma_T c u_B gamma^2 \n\nN(E) is the electron distribution with power law index p equal to\n\nN(E) = kappa E^-p\n\nE is the Einstein's mass equation and dE its derivative such that\n\nE = gamma m_e c^2\n\nand\n\nalpha = fracp-12\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#synchrotron.jl-Documentation","page":"Home","title":"synchrotron.jl Documentation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"dn_e(γ, mps)\nj_syn(ϵ, mps)\nS_syn(ϵ, mps)\nP_syn(ϵ, mps)\nsyncSpec(log_ν, mps)\nsyncPlot(mps)","category":"page"},{"location":"#SyncSSCModel.dn_e-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"Home","title":"SyncSSCModel.dn_e","text":"dn_e(γ, mps)\n\nDifferential electron density at Lorentz factor γ for parameters mps.\n\nThe number of electrons with Lorentz factors in the range gamma to gamma + dgamma is given by dn_e\n\ndn_e = n_e_0 gamma^-p dgamma\n\nwhere\n\ngamma_min le gamma le gamma_max\n\nsee also the equation 7.20 in Rybicki and Lightman (1979)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#SyncSSCModel.j_syn-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"Home","title":"SyncSSCModel.j_syn","text":"j_syn(ϵ, mps)\n\nSynchrotron emissivity at photon energy ϵ for parameters mps.\n\nFor an isotropic electron distribution in a randomly oriented magnetic field, the synchrotron emissivity is (see equation 13 of Dermer et al. (1997); we've changed their H to our B)\n\nj_syn(epsilon Omega x) = fracc sigma_T u_B6 pi epsilon_B left( fracepsilonepsilon_B right)^tiny12 smalln_e left left( fracepsilonepsilon_Bright)^tiny12x right\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#SyncSSCModel.S_syn-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"Home","title":"SyncSSCModel.S_syn","text":"S_syn(ϵ, mps)\n\nSynchrotron Flux Density at observed photon energy ϵ.\n\nThis impliments equation 3 of Dermer et al. (1997).\n\nS_syn(epsilon Omega x) = fracD^3 (1+z) V_b j_syn(fracepsilon (1+z)D Omega x)d_L^2\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#SyncSSCModel.P_syn-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"Home","title":"SyncSSCModel.P_syn","text":"P_syn(ϵ, mps)\n\nSynchrotron Spectral Power Flux at observed photon energy ϵ.\n\nThis is equivalent to \\nu F(\\nu) and presented in equation 23 of Dermer et al. (1997).\n\nP_syn(epsilon Omega x) = epsilon  S_syn\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#SyncSSCModel.syncSpec-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"Home","title":"SyncSSCModel.syncSpec","text":"syncSpec(log_ν, mps)\n\nPopulate the synchrotron spectrum flux_density with frequency bins given by log_νfor parametersmps``\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#SyncSSCModel.syncPlot-Tuple{Any}","page":"Home","title":"SyncSSCModel.syncPlot","text":"syncPlot(mps)\n\nExample synchotron plot for parameters mps.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#Compton.jl-Documentation","page":"Home","title":"Compton.jl Documentation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"j_ssc(ϵ, mps)\nP_ssc(ϵ, mps)\ncomptonSpec(log_ν, mps)\nssc_Plot(mps)","category":"page"},{"location":"#SyncSSCModel.j_ssc-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"Home","title":"SyncSSCModel.j_ssc","text":"j_ssc(ϵ, mps)\n\nSynchrotron Self-Compton (SSC) emissivity at photon energy ϵ for parameters mps.\n\nFor an isotropic power-law electron distribution in a randomly oriented magnetic field, the first order SSC emissivity is given by the equation 20 of Dermer et al. (1997)\n\nj_SSC(epsilon Omega x) = fracc sigma_T^2 n_e0^2 u_B r_b9 pi epsilon_B left( fracepsilonepsilon_B right)^tiny-alpha logSigma_C\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#SyncSSCModel.P_ssc-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"Home","title":"SyncSSCModel.P_ssc","text":"P_ssc(ϵ, mps)\n\nSynchrotron Self-Compton (SSC) Spectral Power Flux at observed photon energy ϵ.\n\nThis is equivalent to νF(ν) and presented in equation 24 of Dermer et al. (1997).\n\nP_ssc(epsilon Omega x) = D^(3+α) fracc sigma_T^2 n_e0^2 u_B r_b V_b9 pi d_L^2 left( 1+z right)^1 - alpha left( fracepsilonepsilon_B right) lnoverlineSigma_c\n\nwhere lnoverlineSigma_c is the transformed Compton-Synchrotron logarithm in equation 25\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#SyncSSCModel.comptonSpec-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"Home","title":"SyncSSCModel.comptonSpec","text":"comptonSpec(log_ν, mps)\n\nPopulate the compton spectrum flux_density with frequency bins given by log_ν for parameters mps\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#SyncSSCModel.ssc_Plot-Tuple{Any}","page":"Home","title":"SyncSSCModel.ssc_Plot","text":"ssc_Plot(mps)\n\nExample synchotron self-compton plot for parameters mps.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"}]
